15/12/2006
VATICAN -- Pope Benedict XVI met on Thursday (December 14th) with Archbishop Christodoulos, head of the Orthodox Church of Greece, to discuss ties between the two churches. Afterwards, the Pope and the Archbishop issued a joint statement noting that religions play a particular role in preserving world peace, and can not be converted into sources of intolerance and violence. In this respect, they vowed to continue and strengthen inter-religious dialogue. (ANA-MPA, AP - 14/12/06) 
